From b54aa08defff7df2dbb19b563599e1a9c9c002d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vera Aletheia <vera@veraaletheia.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 19:05:23 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] report mockup: viewport-agnostic onboarding + mobile
 layout fix

The report mockup at /report-mockup.html had onboarding copy that
only made sense on desktop ("on the left", "on the left rail") plus
a desktop-three-column layout that didn't reflow properly on mobile.

Copy fix:
- "Use ... on the left." -> "Pick a tab ... and open a finding."
- "Open a cluster on the left rail" -> "Open a cluster in the rail"
- "Click a finding row to see it here" -> "Click a finding row to
  view it here"

Layout fix (@media max-width 768px):
- App-header wraps cleanly: logo -> title -> action buttons stacked
- Panel-left (tabs + clusters) becomes the FIRST full-width block
- Canvas (screenshot + spotlight) is SECOND full-width block
- Panel-right (detail) is THIRD full-width block
- Onboarding steps collapse to single column (was 2-col grid)
- Panel tabs scroll horizontally if they overflow
- Bottom-bar wraps instead of squishing

The desktop layout is untouched. Only mobile (<768px) gets the new
stacked order, which matches what a phone user actually experiences.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
