><div class="priority-refs"><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="trust-credibility/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>trust-credibility/F-01</strong> — Trust proof is missing beside the fitment decision</span></div><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="trust-credibility/F-02"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>trust-credibility/F-02</strong> — Social proof appears inconsistently across featured products</span></div><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="pricing/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>pricing/F-01</strong> — Price is visible but value context is not</span></div><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="checkout-flows/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>checkout-flows/F-01</strong> — Checkout convenience cues are buried in the footer</span></div></div></div><div class="priority-card"><div class="priority-card-head"><span class="priority-card-num">3</span><span class="priority-card-title">Make browsing faster once the shopper lands on homepage merch</span></div><div class="priority-card-meta">Fixes 3 findings across 3 clusters (performance-ux, product-media, category-navigation)</div><div class="priority-card-action">Pull a tighter merch module higher on the page and make category/product cards carry clearer fitment and comparison information before any quick-view interaction.</div><div class="priority-refs-label">Underlying findings</div><div class="priority-refs"><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="performance-ux/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>performance-ux/F-01</strong> — Homepage browsing starts after multiple stacked decision layers</span></div><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="product-media/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>product-media/F-01</strong> — Featured cards lean on quick view more than product evidence</span></div><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="category-navigation/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>category-navigation/F-01</strong> — Category shortcuts do not carry the shopper&#39;s vehicle context</span></div></div></div><div class="priority-card"><div class="priority-card-head"><span class="priority-card-num">4</span><span class="priority-card-title">Repair homepage relevance and retention signals</span></div><div class="priority-card-meta">Fixes 2 findings across 2 clusters (content-seo, post-purchase)</div><div class="priority-card-action">Rewrite the homepage metadata around the real vehicle/value proposition, then turn the lower-page retention block into a support-and-lifecycle message instead of newsletter-only capture.</div><div class="priority-refs-label">Underlying findings</div><div class="priority-refs"><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="content-seo/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>content-seo/F-01</strong> — Homepage sends weak relevance signals to search and AI systems</span></div><div class="priority-ref-row" data-fid="post-purchase/F-01"><span class="priority-ref-check" role="checkbox" aria-checked="false"></span><span class="priority-ref-label"><strong>post-purchase/F-01</strong> — Retention is delegated to a newsletter block instead of a support promise</span></div></div></div>
